README.md
     1Рєњlog
     4РєњA Rust library providing a lightweight logging *facade*.
     5Рєњ
      РєњРђд
    19Рєњ## Minimum supported `rustc`
    21Рєњ`1.68.0+`
    22Рєњ
      РєњРђд
    25Рєњ## Usage
    27Рєњ### In libraries
    29РєњLibraries should link only to the `log` crate, and use the provided macros to
    30Рєњlog whatever information will be useful to downstream consumers:
    31Рєњ
    32Рєњ```toml
    33Рєњ[dependencies]
    34Рєњlog = "0.4"
    35Рєњ```
    36Рєњ
    37Рєњ```rust
    38Рєњuse log::{info, trace, warn};
    39Рєњ
    40Рєњpub fn shave_the_yak(yak: &mut Yak) {
    41Рєњ    trace!("Commencing yak shaving");
    42Рєњ
    43Рєњ    loop {
    44Рєњ        match find_a_razor() {
    45Рєњ            Ok(razor) => {
    46Рєњ                info!("Razor located: {razor}");
    47Рєњ                yak.shave(razor);
    48Рєњ                break;
    49Рєњ            }
    50Рєњ            Err(err) => {
    51Рєњ                warn!("Unable to locate a razor: {err}, retrying");
    52Рєњ            }
    53Рєњ        }
    54Рєњ    }
    55Рєњ}
    56Рєњ```
    57Рєњ
    58Рєњ### In executables
    60РєњIn order to produce log output, executables have to use a logger implementation compatible with the facade.
    61РєњThere are many available implementations to choose from, here are some options:
    62Рєњ
    63Рєњ* Simple minimal loggers:
    64Рєњ    * [`env_logger`](https://docs.rs/env_logger/*/env_logger/)
    65Рєњ    * [`colog`](https://docs.rs/colog/*/colog/)
    66Рєњ    * [`simple_logger`](https://docs.rs/simple_logger/*/simple_logger/)
    67Рєњ    * [`simplelog`](https://docs.rs/simplelog/*/simplelog/)
    68Рєњ    * [`pretty_env_logger`](https://docs.rs/pretty_env_logger/*/pretty_env_logger/)
    69Рєњ    * [`stderrlog`](https://docs.rs/stderrlog/*/stderrlog/)
    70Рєњ    * [`flexi_logger`](https://docs.rs/flexi_logger/*/flexi_logger/)
    71Рєњ    * [`call_logger`](https://docs.rs/call_logger/*/call_logger/)
    72Рєњ    * [`std-logger`](https://docs.rs/std-logger/*/std_logger/)
    73Рєњ    * [`structured-logger`](https://docs.rs/structured-logger/latest/structured_logger/)
    74Рєњ    * [`clang_log`](https://docs.rs/clang_log/latest/clang_log)
    75Рєњ    * [`ftail`](https://docs.rs/ftail/latest/ftail/)
      РєњРђд
   106Рєњ## Structured logging
   108РєњIf you enable the `kv` feature, you can associate structured data with your log records:
   109Рєњ
